00:21:26,241 --> 00:21:31,205
So I don't know if anyone else is familiar with this character, but his name is Gudetama

421
00:21:31,485 --> 00:21:36,549
and he's a lazy egg, always with this face of despair and kind of lacking in spunk.

422
00:21:37,490 --> 00:21:43,054
And Gudetama is hard to motivate and has this extremely negative and defeatist attitude.

423
00:21:45,845 --> 00:21:47,846
On his official Twitter account, he writes,

424
00:21:48,387 --> 00:21:50,147
I don't really feel like tweeting every day.

425
00:21:50,447 --> 00:21:51,348
It's such a bother.

426
00:21:51,748 --> 00:21:53,989
I'll do it because the higher-ups tell me to do it,

427
00:21:54,349 --> 00:21:56,190
but I know I'm gonna be eaten in the end.

428
00:21:57,511 --> 00:22:01,112
But here's the thing, Gudetama is super relatable.

429
00:22:01,633 --> 00:22:04,334
Everyone loves him despite his lazy demeanor

430
00:22:04,474 --> 00:22:06,075
and his negative outlook on life.

431
00:22:06,815 --> 00:22:10,998
I want to quickly bring your attention to a couple of games that share similarities

432
00:22:11,058 --> 00:22:12,159
to Gudetama's appeal.

433
00:22:13,420 --> 00:22:17,803
There are more and more creators right now creating weird and personal and really intimate

434
00:22:17,843 --> 00:22:21,106
stuff, but I'm just going to mention two creators that have personally inspired my

435
00:22:21,146 --> 00:22:21,786
work a lot.

436
00:22:22,984 --> 00:22:24,906
So the first one is Nina Freeman,

437
00:22:25,026 --> 00:22:27,168
who is a huge role model for me.

438
00:22:27,308 --> 00:22:30,531
She's maybe the reason why I started making personal games

439
00:22:30,591 --> 00:22:33,293
in the first place, because I saw and played her work,

440
00:22:33,393 --> 00:22:35,415
and it opened my eyes to the possibility

441
00:22:35,435 --> 00:22:40,019
of making really deeply personal and vulnerable stuff.

442
00:22:40,119 --> 00:22:43,983
She recently released Kimmy for Humble Bundle,

443
00:22:44,043 --> 00:22:47,046
and I think the Steam release is gonna come soon,

444
00:22:47,086 --> 00:22:48,707
so definitely check it out when it comes out.

445
00:22:51,237 --> 00:22:53,438
You may also know her other game, Sybil,

446
00:22:53,478 --> 00:22:55,318
which she released like over a year ago.

447
00:22:55,338 --> 00:22:59,140
And Sybil is an autobiographical game

448
00:23:01,001 --> 00:23:02,901
where you play as 19 year old,

449
00:23:04,062 --> 00:23:05,863
you play as a 19 year old girl

450
00:23:07,003 --> 00:23:08,704
who has met this guy online

451
00:23:08,984 --> 00:23:10,544
and falls in love with him basically.

452
00:23:10,644 --> 00:23:14,866
And her relationship with him is revealed

453
00:23:14,926 --> 00:23:17,247
through this MMO that they play together.

454
00:23:17,527 --> 00:23:21,890
And I think this game does a great job of tying in this cute and relatable aesthetic

455
00:23:21,950 --> 00:23:26,753
to deliver this super personal narrative and help players situate themselves in Nina's

456
00:23:26,813 --> 00:23:27,373
point of view.

457
00:23:28,954 --> 00:23:33,397
Another one of her games that I think really showcases this point of cute being relatable

458
00:23:33,437 --> 00:23:35,458
and personable is How Do You Do It?

459
00:23:35,999 --> 00:23:39,941
You're this little girl whose mom steps out of the house and you're curious about sex.

460
00:23:40,181 --> 00:23:43,663
So you try to get an idea of what that's like by playing with dolls.

461
00:23:43,703 --> 00:23:46,585
And I think so many of us have done that as children.

462
00:23:47,146 --> 00:23:50,048
And I really like this game because I think it puts,

463
00:23:50,688 --> 00:23:53,470
it celebrates teenage girls and their sexual agency.

464
00:23:54,151 --> 00:23:56,933
And it's finally this game which gives women

465
00:23:57,413 --> 00:23:59,515
a sense of autonomy without having to relate

466
00:23:59,575 --> 00:24:01,696
their self-worth to what a man thinks of them.

467
00:24:02,097 --> 00:24:04,218
I think it does a really great job

468
00:24:04,318 --> 00:24:06,440
using this cute visual aesthetic

469
00:24:06,540 --> 00:24:08,341
and these goofy, playful mechanics

470
00:24:08,802 --> 00:24:10,523
that just help get the point across.

471
00:24:11,484 --> 00:24:14,646
And this aesthetic just really resonated with me,

472
00:24:14,826 --> 00:24:16,748
both as a designer and as a player.

473
00:24:18,109 --> 00:24:20,671
Another developer who I really like a lot

474
00:24:20,831 --> 00:24:23,153
is Lea Schoenfelder.

475
00:24:23,173 --> 00:24:26,436
You might have heard this game she made with Peter Liu

476
00:24:26,796 --> 00:24:28,637
for the Kinect called Perfect Woman.

477
00:24:29,638 --> 00:24:32,540
And the main mechanic here is body bending.

478
00:24:32,641 --> 00:24:35,403
So you start as a fetus in your mother's womb,

479
00:24:35,883 --> 00:24:37,584
and you perform in front of a Kinect

480
00:24:37,705 --> 00:24:39,986
to mimic various poses that appear on screen.

481
00:24:40,887 --> 00:24:41,967
to act out this character.

482
00:24:42,507 --> 00:24:45,668
It also uses these super goofy and bright visuals

483
00:24:45,908 --> 00:24:48,469
to poke fun and lighten this more serious subject matter,

484
00:24:48,529 --> 00:24:50,610
allowing us to engage and maybe think about

485
00:24:50,630 --> 00:24:52,910
what it means to be a woman in this society.

486
00:24:54,611 --> 00:24:56,351
Leia also made this game called Oot.

487
00:24:57,674 --> 00:25:02,198
The goal is simple, you have to have sex with as many men

488
00:25:02,538 --> 00:25:03,599
before you get married.

489
00:25:04,499 --> 00:25:06,441
And the structure has a lot to say about

490
00:25:06,581 --> 00:25:10,104
the sexual constraints that women find themselves in.

491
00:25:10,484 --> 00:25:12,546
You know, it does such a great job intertwining

492
00:25:12,626 --> 00:25:13,987
gay mechanics and narrative.

493
00:25:14,607 --> 00:25:17,489
And the cuteness comes across here with this sense of humor,

494
00:25:17,550 --> 00:25:20,192
which effectively allows us to deliver

495
00:25:20,252 --> 00:25:21,613
these more serious topics.

496
00:25:22,013 --> 00:25:26,057
All these games that I just mentioned are games that use this cute aesthetic to get

497
00:25:26,117 --> 00:25:32,142
across these deeply personal and intimate subjects. Anyway, let's talk about Consume Me.

498
00:25:32,983 --> 00:25:37,087
Like I mentioned before, it's a personal game about my experience with dieting.

499
00:25:38,368 --> 00:25:42,572
It's still currently a work in progress and mostly made up of prototypes that

